<br>
Then you get the retards who are in awe of call forwarding.  &quot;How does that work?  You can answer their phone but you're not in their office?  I think you're lying.  Come open the door and pay us, I know you're in there, you're making things up.&quot;<br>
<br>
And the people who talk like they have a mouthful of marbles, I guess that's cool in some social circles, because once I tell them that I can't understand them, they talk semi-normally and I can make out words rather than mumbling.<br>
<br>
Ooh ooh I hate when women call who think they're all big and bad and think I'm trying to rip them off because their women!  They're all like &quot;I want to talk to them NOW I know they're in the office, so put me through!&quot;  That's when I hit the delete button and go offline.<br>
<br>
I actually did have one guy say &quot;hey, you're the big bouncer lookin' guy that chills outside in front of the store right?&quot;  And I played along because I thought it was funny.<br>
<br>
Anyways.  The temp service workers of America are certainly a bright bunch.<br>
